result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th) and Operating with PAC of .02 or More (5th+) [Modifiers: Penalty-Operating While Intoxicate (5+), Penalties for Felonies-Class "H" Felony]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th) and the other charge, Operating with PAC of .02 or More (5th+) [Modifiers: Penalty-Operating While Intoxicate (5+), Penalties for Felonies-Class "H" Felony] was dismissed by the court.

  • Willis Joseph Beauvais was found guilty of OWI (4th), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
